If it is loot both of my toons can use or vendor trash rolls, I'm rolling with both. Let me justify:<br>
<br>
1) Part of it is my combination. A cleric/warrior combo has got to be the easiest hydra combo in EQ. Hitting taunt when the mob looks away and pressing my CH macro when tank is at X percent doesn't require a lot of talent, and I can carry on normal conversations during normal grind and ninja afk with the best of them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
An average bard or hybrid does more actual work and is less communicative with one toon than I am with two. Diminished skill really isn't a good argument in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>my</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> case, but a bard/chanter combo would definitely be less able to play those classes to the best of their ability.<br>
<br>
2) I never force my hydraing on any group. I'll gladly dump either toon to make room for another person that can cover either role. Only reason I play with both is that for most of the groups I join, both are needed.<br>
<br>
3) Both of my toons are equally gimp/uber (whatever your perspective is). Not a clear advantage in gear or level on either, and neither would hold a group down with gimpyness more than any other warrior or cleric with the same gear/levels.<br>
<br>
4) Both need gear, but I'm not selfish about it. If the loot is CLR usable and not WAR, I only roll CLR. Same goes for my warrior. They are both plate classes, so there is some overlap, but not often as usually there are vast differences in what I'm looking for for each toon. For clear example of what I'm talking about, when a parchment drops, my warrior doesn't roll, but my cleric does.<br>
<br>
5) You encourage hydras to lie if you don't let hydras roll with both. With all of the other crap people do to each other in this game, this extra element really isn't needed.<br>
<br>
The reason this is probably an issue is the fear that a hydra will use two rolls to get one toon upgrades. I can perfectly understand this fear, and I find that practice deplorable. By all means, don't group with these dickheads.<br>
<br>
I've hopefully made the case that I'm not one of them.<br>
<br>
